341    /**
342    * Collect parameter names referenced after a non-local side-effect.
343    *
344    * Assumptions:
345    * - We assume parameters are not modified in the function body
346    * (that is checked separately).
347    * - There are no inner functions (also checked separately).
348    *
349    * As we are trying to replace parameters with there passed in values
350    * we are interested in anything that may affect those value. So, ignoring
351    * changes to local variables, we look for things that may affect anything
352    * outside the local-state. Once such a side-effect is seen any following
353    * reference to the function parameters are collected. These will need
354    * to be assigned to temporaries to prevent changes to their value as would
355    * have happened during the function call.
356    *
357    * To properly handle loop structures all references to the function
358    * parameters are recorded and the decision to keep or throw away those
359    * references is deferred until exiting the loop structure.
360    */
